# This project does not require any environment variables today.
# The contact form function only uses Firebase Admin SDK:
# - Locally, the Firebase emulators provide the project context.
# - In production, Firebase injects the project context automatically.
#
# That means you do NOT need to copy the old web config here:
# - apiKey
# - appId
# - measurementId
# Those values are no longer used by the backend.
#
# When should you create a real .env file in functions/?
# Only if this backend starts depending on custom configuration,
# such as:
# - an external API base URL
# - a feature flag
# - a third-party token for local development
#
# Local development:
# 1. Copy this file to functions/.env
# 2. Fill in only the variables your function code actually reads
# 3. Do not commit functions/.env
#
# Production on Firebase:
# - A local functions/.env file is NOT uploaded automatically.
# - If the backend needs real production configuration,
#   you must define it in Firebase separately.
# - For sensitive values, use Firebase Secret Manager / Functions secrets.
# - For non-sensitive config, use the Firebase Functions environment config supported by your setup.
#
# Current status for this repository:
# - No variables are required.
# - You do not need to configure anything manually in Firebase for this function to access Firestore.

# Example only. Not used by the current code.
# EXTERNAL_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com
# EXTERNAL_API_TOKEN=replace-me
